---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Labs"
  description="Early interactive prototypes of the worldbuilding tool in development."
  hideTray={true}
>
  <h1>Labs</h1>
  <p>
    Working prototypes from the worldbuilding tool currently in design — a
    world wiki where every generator on this site can add a permanent, linked,
    editable page to <em>your</em> world, navigated from a world map that zooms
    from continent to dungeon. These are throwaway demos built to test design
    decisions, not the product; expect rough edges, and expect them to change.
  </p>

  <h2><a href="/labs/hex-zoom.html">Hex map zoom</a></h2>
  <p>
    The map concept: one continuous world under three hex tiers (60-mile,
    6-mile, 500-ft) that cross-fade as you zoom, Google-Maps style, down to a
    5-ft dungeon site. Every hex's terrain is generated from a seed on the fly
    — nothing you see is stored. Drag to pan, scroll to zoom, click a hex to
    inspect it, and dive toward the ⚔ marker to enter the dungeon.
  </p>

  <h2><a href="/labs/world-viewer.html">World wiki viewer</a></h2>
  <p>
    The wiki concept, rendering a small test world ("Vessia"): pages for a
    region, town, tavern, innkeeper, and a quest whose villain, lair, and
    prize are real cross-linked pages. Follow the mention links, check the
    backlinks, toggle <strong>Player View</strong> to watch secrets vanish,
    and open the tavern or the barrow to see battle-map floors with placed
    items.
  </p>

  <p>
    The full plans live in the repository under
    <a href="https://github.com/seriousd6/Storyteller/tree/main/docs/everdeep"
      >docs/everdeep</a
    >. Feedback is welcome —
    <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/seriousd6/">u/seriousd6</a>.
  </p>
</Base>
